B = \begin{pmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{pmatrix}
\frac{c}{a}
\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\ -\frac{c}{a} & 1 \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} a & b \\ 0 & d-\frac{bc}{a} \end{pmatrix}
\{P_1,\ldots,P_n\}
P_n P_{n-1} \cdots P_1 B = I
\begin{align*} P_n P_{n-1}\cdots P_1 A &= P_n P_{n-1}\cdots P_1 BC \\  &= IC\\  &= C \end{align*}
